parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator can cause the brake pedal to extend to the floorboard, leading to extended braking distances, which can increase the risk of accidents and compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal extends to the floorboard
a loud audible sound is detected
the brake warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
the message "Replace Actuator" is displayed
clicking or popping noises are heard when applying the brakes
the brakes feel difficult to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting and sticking of interior surfaces can cause discomfort, distraction, and potentially affect breathing due to strong odors, which can compromise driver safety and overall vehicle experience.
symptoms: The interior surfaces (dashboard
door panels
steering wheel center) feel sticky
melt
or disintegrate
especially during warm days or when exposed to sunlight; strong
unpleasant odors are emitted; surfaces reflect sunlight
causing glare.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the vehicle to stop abruptly, leading to potential accidents or loss of control, and result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle stops abruptly; warning lights for VCS
brake
and ABS appear on the dashboard; the ABS control module needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rust Corrosion on Front Passenger Door
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust corrosion on the front passenger door can lead to structural weakening, compromising the safety of the vehicle and its occupants.
symptoms: Small bubble spot or rust spot on the bottom middle front passenger door
which can spread and worsen over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticky and melting interior panels can cause discomfort, distraction, and mess while driving, potentially leading to accidents. Additionally, it can decrease the resale value of the vehicle.
symptoms: Interior door panels
glove compartment
upper dash
and lower dash become sticky and shiny when exposed to sunlight
with surfaces disintegrating or melting over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Stalling with Illuminated Warning Lights
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle stalling with illuminated warning lights can cause accidents, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
and all warning lights on the dashboard illuminate.
